  "title": "Chinese Language Teacher (Secondary School)",
  "description": "<p>Education: Minimum Bachelor's Degree in Chinese</p>\n<p>Experience: One to two years</p>\n<p>Working hours : Monday to Friday 10 am – 7 pm; Saturday to Sunday 8:30 am – 6:45 pm ( 42.5 hours in total)</p>\n<p>Must cross schools (2 outlet )</p>\n<p>Working on Saturdays and Sundays is required</p>\n<p>Two days off per week (Monday to Friday)</p>\n<p>annual leave 14 days; starting from the second year, add one day, up to a maximum of 21 days .</p>\n<p>Flower Red : Individual performance bonus</p>\n<p>Health Rewards</p>\n<p>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</p>\n<p>Job Description</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct lessons in accordance with centre curriculum.</li>\n  <li>Plan and develop teaching materials.</li>\n  <li>Prepare student progress report.</li>\n  <li>Assist in centre events and activities.</li>\n  <li>Communicate effectively with parents by providing regular updates on students.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Job Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree in Chinese holder with at least 2 years of relevant working experience</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li>\n  <li>Competence in PC skills (MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li>\n  <li>5 days a week (required to work on Saturday &amp; Sunday)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Chan Wei Wen, Mervyn (Reg. No: R25149588)   ST Venture EmPloyment Agency (EA License No: 09C5583)  Please send an updated resume to stvea888@gmail.com if you are keen to apply for this position</p>",
